text: It was a bit expensive for the mixed rice, yes of course, I've ordered fish and meat egg but some stall is about $9 plus. I asked for less rice, dun understand why the staff shook the head, and  showed the expression of impatience. The cost is $10.70, and the fish is $4.5. Well, I'm not eating this stall again. Will try other stalls. The other 2 coffee shops opposite the road are newer and better foods.

Zi char, Roasted pork/ herbal duck and Economical stall are okay.
The toilet is often dirty and smelly. Cleanliness need to improve.
I only order take away most of the time.

Average neighborhood coffee shop. The economical bee hoon stall offers food at reasonable prices for breakfast with good portion size. The economical rice stall offer good variety of dishes at  reasonable prices. The Indian Muslim stall prices are unreasonable and offer less variety and taste. For Indian Muslim food, better off  walking a short distance to the adjacent block 158 Indian Muslim Coffee shop.
Most stalls the food are average except for the economy rice which is not bad. The chicken rice is below par standard.
